                        "name": "1.E.1 Number of non-profit organizations per 10 thous. population",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 1. No poverty",
                      
                        "priority": "Development of social and solidarity economy",
                      
                        "definition": "The number of formalised entities, institutionally separate from public administration and self-governing entities whose activities are characterised by voluntary participation and non-profit nature, per 10 thousand population.",
                      
                        "unit": "pieces",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "The non-profit sector is a group of entities that meet the following conditions:- are formalized to an appropriate degree (e.g. as a result of registration with the appropriate office), or at least their goals, method of operation and structure are permanent,- are institutionally separate from public administration,- are non-profit (they operate not for profit and do not distribute any surplus among their members, employees, etc.),- are self-governing (the authorities and directions of activity are determined within the organization),- are characterized by voluntary participation in the organization's activities.The group studied includes: active associations and similar social organizations, foundations, social religious entities, economic and professional self-government, and employers' organizations.",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland",
                      
                        "availability": "Since 2022 data in two-year cycles",
                      
